<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 18 at 8:22AM CST  by NWS Shreveport</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southeastern Rusk,
northern Nacogdoches and northwestern Shelby Counties through 900 AM
CST...
At 821 AM CST, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Trawick, or 14 miles north of Nacogdoches, moving east at 40 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Timpson, Garrison, Trawick, Cushing, Appleby, Arcadia, Looneyville
and Stockman.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
